news.title: Hi-Tech Pipes aims 10 lakh tonne production capacity by FY25
news.para: Hi-Tech Pipes also announced commissioning of its Sanand unit-II Phase-1 at Gujarat and establishment of new greenfield unit-III at Sikandrabad (UP) and Sanand Unit-II Phase-2.

news.title: Gmada yet to pay relief for land acquired in Mohali sector 101
news.para: They have now threatened that if the authority does not take any concrete action in this regard till January 31, then they would stage a major protest outside the Gmada Bhawan.

news.title: Nashik: Allotment of smaller plots by MIDC soon
news.para: An MIDC official, while talking to TOI, said two highly reputed firms, including a state-owned oil marketing company, have decided to invest Rs 2,500 crore for setting up a pharma company and manufacturing cryogenic tanks at the new industrial estate.

news.title: Gurugram civic body directs officials to complete checks on property tax data in two days
news.para: For this, the corporation will rope in market associations, residents welfare associations (RWAs) and residents to set up camps to complete the process.

news.title: Gujarat: NA certification process likely to be removed from areas with town planning schemes
news.para: After receiving the feedback that the NA certification process was extremely cumbersome and must be reformed, the committee submitted its recommendations to the government.

news.title: Eighteen months after SC order, demolition drive in Faridabad Aravalis kicks off
news.para: The department has identified 600 such illegal structures in Ankhir and Mewal Maharajpur villages of the district. Land in these villages falls under Section 4 (special orders) of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA), which deems an area as forest land under the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980.

news.title: Hyderabad: Fate of 30,000 two-BHKs in limbo as GHMC awaits Rs 1,500 crore to finish pending work
news.para: As these 2-BHK houses were launched in the previous government’s tenure, the GHMC is in a dilemma over taking up construction works for 30,000 plus units until the new government sanctions the budget to resume the activity.

news.title: Gulshan Homz buys 2.5-acre land in Noida for Rs 150 crore
news.para: The company, which has another commercial project in the same sector, plans to develop one million square feet there.

news.title: Mumbai: Two more FIRs against Supreme Constructions directors
news.para: With the new FIRs, the number of cases against Tekchandani, against whom the police have issued a look-out circular (LOC), touched five.

news.title: Keystone Realtors to redevelop two societies in Mumbai
news.para: Boman Irani, chairman and managing director of the company said, “We are happy to announce that we are chosen as redevelopment partner by two societies in the vibrant locality of Malad West on the combined land spanning over 12,120 sq meters and boasting a combined GDV of about Rs. 1200 crore."

news.title: Oberoi Realty's net profit dips 48.74% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Oberoi Realty's consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,082.85 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 34.43 per cent from Rs 1,651.50 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Choice Hotels nominates board directors in hostile Wyndham bid
news.para: It is Choice's latest attempt to break a stalemate after trying for most of the last year to negotiate a deal with Wyndham, which has rebuffed the bid as low-premium and fraught with antitrust risk. Wyndham has also raised concerns about the combined company carrying too much debt and a slowdown in Choice's business.

news.title: SRG Housing Finance's net profit up 48.32% in Q3 FY24
news.para: SRG Housing Finance's consolidated total income stood at Rs 32.20 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 35.81 per cent from Rs 23.71 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sobha approves issuance of equity shares upto Rs 2,000 crore
news.para: In a separate regulatory filing, Sobha informed that Lalit Lahoty has been appointed as the executive vice president- Business Development of the company with immediate effect.

news.title: Nashik civic body's property tax collection centres to remain open on holidays
news.para: The civic body has also appealed to the people to clear their property and water tax dues at the earliest. Failure to make the payment will lead to confiscation of properties and snapping of water connections.

news.title: Ludhiana: Builder among three booked in Rs 3.34 crore fraud
news.para: The accused were identified as Jatinder Kumar Malhotra of Guru Nanak Dev Nagar; Raju Taneja, a realtor from near Ganda Nullah area and Naresh Wadhwa of dairy complex at Tajpur road.

news.title: Delhi: MCD & DDA penalised for dumping construction & demolition waste
news.para: ​In the report, DPCC stated to have issued a show cause notice to Delhi Development Authority (DDA) and Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) and an environmental compensation of Rs 1 lakh was imposed.

news.title: Kolhapur property tax defaulters to get relief
news.para: Civic chief K Manjulekshmi took this decision on Sunday. “Defaulters clearing their dues before Feb 15 will get a 50% waiver on the fine amount. The waiver will reduce to 30% if the dues are cleared between Feb 16 and March 15.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh builders condemn hike in sand price
news.para: ​Sand mining has become rampant at Chevitikallu, Vani Atkuru and Munneru rivulet. A few gangs swung into action in November last and are selling sand without proper way bills.

news.title: Don't transfer property execution cases to civil courts, HC tells Odisha RERA
news.para: The two-judge bench of acting Chief Justice B R Sarangi and Justice M S Raman sought ORERA’s response on revisiting the practice adopted in execution cases after it claimed it was unable to implement its orders.
